TWO Lanarkshire firms have been recognised in the Oscars of the Scottish food and drink industry.They were selected from a record breaking 239 entries and a shortlist of 50 businesses to take the titles at the Scotland Food &amp; Drink Excellence Awards 2015.A.G.Barr, makers of Irn Bru won the non-alcoholic drink category while Dawnfresh Seafoods picked up the investing in people award and the gong for environmental sustainability.